<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A British woman was allegedly raped by three men in Italy and threatened to jump off a balcony after the ordeal, local media says. </p>

<p>The 32-year-old tourist called police from a holiday home in Lecce after she was allegedly attacked in a different apartment by young men she had spent the evening with.</p>

<p>According to Lecce Prima, she returned to where she was staying near the Piazza Sant'Oronzo and appeared poised to jump off a building as dawn broke. </p>

<p>She was spotted by alarmed passers-by who called the police, who brought the woman to safety and took her to hospital.  </p>

<p>A British woman threatened to jump from a balcony near the Piazza Sant'Oronzo (file image) in Lecce after allegedly being raped by three men, local reports say </p>

<p>After being rescued, the woman told police officers and hospital doctors about the alleged sex attack by three men.  </p>

<p>Italian detectives are now looking at surveillance camera footage from the piazza and its surroundings as they investigate the case.  </p>

<p>Reports say she was staying with a friend and had been with that person earlier in the evening, but they separated before the alleged attack.  </p>

<p>After meeting 'a group of other young people' and drinking with them she was allegedly raped in an apartment where they had spent the evening.    </p>

<p>On returning to her holiday home, the woman reportedly fell into a rage and her screams could be heard in nearby buildings. </p>

<p>The investigation is ongoing.  </p>

<p>For confidential support call the Samaritans on 116123 or visit a local Samaritans branch, see www.samaritans.org for details. </p>
